I have a Kodak Camera (10.2 Megapixels)... Kodak AF 5x OPTICAL LENS... how do I
pause it while recording?<EOS> 

I have a Kodak Camera (10.2 Megapixels)... Kodak AF 5x OPTICAL LENS... how do I
pause it while recording?<EOS> 

You don't... there's no such thing as "pause" in digital recording.<EOS> That's
because of the buffer that holds the data until it's ready to be recorded to the
memory card.<EOS> When you press the button to stop recording the data is moved from
the buffer to the memory card - no pause.<EOS> All you can do is take each section
(individual video) and edit them together on software.<EOS> 

